{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8c0752bb-fd1c-43cb-8624-b40cd49f16f8","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` flag becomes `--filter` on the **MTP runner**, but the syntax differs:\n\n| Old (VSTest) | New (MTP / xUnit v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` ✅ same |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `Trait=Category=Smoke` |\n| `&` (AND) | `&` ✅ same |\n\nYour new command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 2. Why `Category=Smoke` stops working\n\nIn VSTest, `Category` was a well-known alias that mapped to xUnit's `Trait(\"Category\", …)`. MTP doesn't have that alias — you must use the generic `Trait=<name>=<value>` format.\n\n### Quick sanity check\n\nYou can also run the MTP executable directly (since `OutputType` is `Exe`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"48cf8e21-75ec-4bdb-a3be-4e193783eb4e","outputTokens":316},"id":"32add021-9ff2-4f3a-8486-aec8207af554","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:58:22.992Z","parentId":"8754f6ad-9b96-44a1-a149-b74b6df1a0e3"}
